## This commit (stage 3/10: objects/tables/files/refs)
Object CRUD with tombstones, version indexes, latest-alias bookkeeping,
tags/aliases, digest-addressed tables, files. Storage sizes are
uncompressed dump lengths exactly like CH reports them: _ObjRec records
val_dump_len=len(json_val of sorted dumps), table rows record
len(json.dumps(row)), files len(content). objs_query only computes
size_bytes when include_storage_size is set. _read_internal_obj_ref lands
here with refs_read_batch (its first use); the expanded-ref filter/sort
machinery that also uses it is stage 5.

